	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2832369458" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2832369458" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Claire!</p><p>Welcome to Symfony! :) You did a great job creating the database in sqlite. In fact, in the future, you might even be able to do a little less work - you shouldn't need to create the aqua_note_database file - Doctrine should even create that when you run doctrine:database:create :).</p><p>But anyways, one tricky thing with sqlite is that it doesn't have a fancy "mysql" command line tool. There a few GUI tools for visualizing an SQLite database (just google for them - I don't have a favorite, and they're dependent on your OS). OR, there is a better idea :). Symfony has an bin/console command that will make a raw SQL query for you. Try this:</p><p></p><pre><code><br>bin/console doctrine:query:sql 'DESCRIBE genus'<br></code></pre><p></p><p>It's not quite as convenient as the "mysql" utility, since you need to prefix everything with the "bin/console doctrine:query:sql", but it works awesome!</p><p>Let me know if it helps!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
